# =============================================================================
# Kubernetes misconfig — ACCEPTED RISK (postgres DBs only)
# =============================================================================
# KSV014 (readOnlyRootFilesystem) and KSV118 (default security context) on the
# auth-db and transaction-db postgres deployments.
#
# The official postgres:14 image cannot run under readOnlyRootFilesystem: its
# entrypoint runs initdb, which chmod's /var/lib/postgresql/data — an operation
# that fails as "Operation not permitted" under a read-only root + non-root user
# (verified: CrashLoopBackOff). Supporting it would require switching to a
# non-root-built image (e.g. Bitnami), which is out of scope.
#
# Risk acceptance rationale:
#  - The DB pods are internal-only (NetworkPolicy restricts ingress to their own
#    service; no external exposure).
#  - All three APPLICATION services (the actual attack surface) ARE fully
#    hardened: readOnlyRootFilesystem + runAsNonRoot + seccomp + drop ALL.
#  - Zero CRITICAL findings; these are HIGH on internal data-tier pods.
#
# Recheck: evaluate a non-root postgres image in a future iteration.
# =============================================================================
AVD-KSV-0014
AVD-KSV-0118
